A former worker of Owoyemi Super Store, along Idiroko road, Sango-Ota, Ola Adeoye, has been arrested by the Ogun State police command for burgling his former employer’s store. The 28-year-old Adeoye was nabbed after the Sango police station received a distress call at about 1:45am that the store had been burgled, DAILY POST learnt. The distress call led the DPO of Sango/Ota, CSP Godwin Idehai and his men to the scene. Four men arrested for burgling phone shop, robbing owner in Osun “On getting to the scene, it was discovered that the two-storey building was broken into through the balcony of the second floor, and the MD’s office had been ransacked, with an attempt to break the company’s safe,” the Ogun State Police Public Relations Officer, Abimbola Oyeyemi, said on Thursday. According to Oyeyemi, after diligent search, Adeola was seen hiding in a water tank, from where he was arrested. “On interrogation, he confessed being a former staff of the company, and that he was sacked a month ago,” it was said. Meanwhile, the state Commissioner of Police, Edward Ajogun, has ordered that the suspect be charged to court as soon as investigation is concluded. Idiroko border closed despite forceful reopening by Yoruba nation agitators